    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-md-template-js",
    "path": "/blogs/this-blog-is-written-on-i-pad",
    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"to-give-it-a-try\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#to-give-it-a-try\" aria-label=\"to give it a try permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>To Give it a Try</h2>\n<p>Two days ago saw a <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vPigsZ-zk1g\">Youtube video</a> about <a href=\"https://github.com/features/codespaces\">Github Codespaces</a>. I was impressed by the potential of the new software developing workflow introduced by this web IDE. However, I was also telling myself - OK, there must be a lot of limitations because, well, it's new, it's on cloud, it's in a browser, there must be something I cannot do, at least at this point of time. In the end it will break my workflow and I will move back to native VSCode.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>I was wrong, and right.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"hands-on\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#hands-on\" aria-label=\"hands on permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Hands on</h2>\n<p>By navigating to my blog's github repo page, I am able to find a tab for Codespaces under \"Code\" buttom.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 399px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9cc6c61030d441e1c924fb17120502dd/a307d/8dac47c20664623c2c9f7481e1a2f849063d4a0a9bb1e46993ea55c968b297c3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 73.06122448979592%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 1\"\n        title=\"picture 1\"\n        src=\"/static/9cc6c61030d441e1c924fb17120502dd/a307d/8dac47c20664623c2c9f7481e1a2f849063d4a0a9bb1e46993ea55c968b297c3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9cc6c61030d441e1c924fb17120502dd/86a2e/8dac47c20664623c2c9f7481e1a2f849063d4a0a9bb1e46993ea55c968b297c3.png 245w,\n/static/9cc6c61030d441e1c924fb17120502dd/a307d/8dac47c20664623c2c9f7481e1a2f849063d4a0a9bb1e46993ea55c968b297c3.png 399w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 399px) 100vw, 399px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In the above image, there is already an existing Codespace. We can select the existing Codespace or, \"Configure and create codespace\":\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 782px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e655af66d37aff7b95380c6c5015fc03/2e195/dad7345b8cdf9a347061c5a23a531fb48f4ca9e33395be570e70523a199522c6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70.61224489795919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 2\"\n        title=\"picture 2\"\n        src=\"/static/e655af66d37aff7b95380c6c5015fc03/2e195/dad7345b8cdf9a347061c5a23a531fb48f4ca9e33395be570e70523a199522c6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e655af66d37aff7b95380c6c5015fc03/86a2e/dad7345b8cdf9a347061c5a23a531fb48f4ca9e33395be570e70523a199522c6.png 245w,\n/static/e655af66d37aff7b95380c6c5015fc03/41d3c/dad7345b8cdf9a347061c5a23a531fb48f4ca9e33395be570e70523a199522c6.png 490w,\n/static/e655af66d37aff7b95380c6c5015fc03/2e195/dad7345b8cdf9a347061c5a23a531fb48f4ca9e33395be570e70523a199522c6.png 782w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 782px) 100vw, 782px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The configurations say everything. But one more interesting thing is, while waiting for the space creation, I found <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/codespaces/setting-up-your-project-for-codespaces/introduction-to-dev-containers\">a wiki</a> displaying one more configuration for Dev Container, providing opportunity for container customization.</p>\n<p>Then, my workspace with a VSCode is opened in browser and by signed in my vscode sync account, everything looks familiar, just like my native VSCode work space.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/42d2a79c08c609f8f9efcc18447024c8/c0ebd/0f7195a4498b89d5fe1abb21bb375957c046329cdff6e439f48deb25e72c364d.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 67.3469387755102%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 3\"\n        title=\"picture 3\"\n        src=\"/static/42d2a79c08c609f8f9efcc18447024c8/d30ee/0f7195a4498b89d5fe1abb21bb375957c046329cdff6e439f48deb25e72c364d.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/42d2a79c08c609f8f9efcc18447024c8/86a2e/0f7195a4498b89d5fe1abb21bb375957c046329cdff6e439f48deb25e72c364d.png 245w,\n/static/42d2a79c08c609f8f9efcc18447024c8/41d3c/0f7195a4498b89d5fe1abb21bb375957c046329cdff6e439f48deb25e72c364d.png 490w,\n/static/42d2a79c08c609f8f9efcc18447024c8/d30ee/0f7195a4498b89d5fe1abb21bb375957c046329cdff6e439f48deb25e72c364d.png 980w,\n/static/42d2a79c08c609f8f9efcc18447024c8/c0ebd/0f7195a4498b89d5fe1abb21bb375957c046329cdff6e439f48deb25e72c364d.png 1177w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span><br>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/dd507/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.244897959183675%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 4\"\n        title=\"picture 4\"\n        src=\"/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/d30ee/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/86a2e/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png 245w,\n/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/41d3c/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png 490w,\n/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/d30ee/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png 980w,\n/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/1134b/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png 1470w,\n/static/9ca75df3de284ac73a59480285161bc5/dd507/3206fe1ed27408c746efe8617cadee39d4a9b072948d2279b9d3af532bff66f5.png 1528w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Crazy right? My cosmetic plugins - <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=PKief.material-icon-theme\">Material Icon Theme</a> and <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=vscodevim.vim\">VIM</a> plugin also work (look) like a charm.</p>\n<p>Even more, developing preview is also impressive. My blog is a Gatsby website. Simply running <code class=\"language-text\">npm run start</code>, Codespaces hosts a \"local\" preview server in the container and does a port forwarding to public network. You can configure the behavior of port forwarding:\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 758px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/910be981116f961f8f309ef023b4ef5f/c8e86/c3014f60e77dc5c0b033026c0dd3de033cdaa3a624e9d9384b7e90b8a541da9e.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.69387755102041%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 5\"\n        title=\"picture 5\"\n        src=\"/static/910be981116f961f8f309ef023b4ef5f/c8e86/c3014f60e77dc5c0b033026c0dd3de033cdaa3a624e9d9384b7e90b8a541da9e.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/910be981116f961f8f309ef023b4ef5f/86a2e/c3014f60e77dc5c0b033026c0dd3de033cdaa3a624e9d9384b7e90b8a541da9e.png 245w,\n/static/910be981116f961f8f309ef023b4ef5f/41d3c/c3014f60e77dc5c0b033026c0dd3de033cdaa3a624e9d9384b7e90b8a541da9e.png 490w,\n/static/910be981116f961f8f309ef023b4ef5f/c8e86/c3014f60e77dc5c0b033026c0dd3de033cdaa3a624e9d9384b7e90b8a541da9e.png 758w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Everything is the same as my current workflow for writing blog in my native VS code! TBH, I am impressed. One of my worries when I decided to host my website using Gatsby is, I have to sit down at my desk and write. Now, looks like I can write blog using my iPad or, my phone!</p>\n<p>And this is what I get on iPad, like a dream, right?\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/e1596/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.10204081632654%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 6\"\n        title=\"picture 6\"\n        src=\"/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/4012a/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/a0fb2/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg 245w,\n/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/6b254/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg 490w,\n/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/4012a/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg 980w,\n/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/38a9e/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg 1470w,\n/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/82b8c/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg 1960w,\n/static/1ef917ba7ea728b8be6d13f7c0345bd3/e1596/53dbd88ec80fbc1019957bd07b2bb908bd5924f615a0791cbfe75bc6c824c709.jpg 2048w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>However, there is a \"however\".</p>\n<h2 id=\"dev-workflow-my-version\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#dev-workflow-my-version\" aria-label=\"dev workflow my version permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dev Workflow, My Version</h2>\n<p>Before talking about \"however\", noting down my understanding of the workflow of using Codespace:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A Codespace is equivalent to a host or a virtual machine. It provides you a container with VS Code as an interface. You can install <code class=\"language-text\">apt</code> pacakges to the container.</li>\n<li>After the creation of Codespace, your selected git branch will be fetched. The logic of using Git is the same as what it is like on the local machine.</li>\n<li>Same Codespace is synchronized in real time. If you have multiple browser opened and edit in one of them, other browsers will see the same change in real time. If a seperate working branch is needed, you need to create a new Codespace container.</li>\n<li>To preview the change, as long as the framework you used provide a way to preview in localhost, Codespace will do port forwarding automatically and enable you to preview your change in a \"public\" url.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"however\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#however\" aria-label=\"however permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>However...</h2>\n<h3 id=\"low-marker--font-issue\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#low-marker--font-issue\" aria-label=\"low marker  font issue permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><low-marker /> Font Issue</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Font of terminal on iPad is problematic\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 980px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4eebb069f8b19a8943ac0b16d3ed59f1/e1596/5c9256b55297de2743fa9a1ae4c6339bd1ee63a51bb08f25626dfad9c62caf63.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75.10204081632654%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"picture 7\"\n        title=\"picture 7\"\n        src=\"/static/4eebb069f8b19a8943ac0b16d3ed59f1/4012a/5c9256b55297de2743fa9a1ae4c6339bd1ee63a51bb08f25626dfad9c62caf63.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4eebb069f8b19a8943ac0b16d3ed59f1/a0fb2/5c9256b55297de2743fa9a1ae4c6339bd1ee63a51bb08f25626dfad9c62caf63.jpg 245w,\n/static/4eebb069f8b19a8943ac0b16d3ed59f1/6b254/5c9256b55297de2743fa9a1ae4c6339bd1ee63a51bb08f25626dfad9c62caf63.jpg 490w,\n/static/4eebb069f8b19a8943ac0b16d3ed59f1/4012a/5c9256b55297de2743fa9a1ae4c6339bd1ee63a